<Project Sdk="Dalamud.NET.Sdk/15.0.0">

  <PropertyGroup>
    <Author>LastOnionKnight</Author>
    <Name>GearGoblin</Name>
    <InternalName>GearGoblin</InternalName>
    <AssemblyVersion>0.4.5.0</AssemblyVersion>
    <FileVersion>0.4.5.0</FileVersion>
    <Version>0.4.5.0</Version>
    <MinimumDalamudVersion>15.0.0</MinimumDalamudVersion>
    <Punchline>BiS planner + native Character panel takeover. Replaces CharacterPanelRefined with compact derived stats, breakpoint hints, real GCD, Tenacity/Piety rows, and a built-in Materia Advisor.</Punchline>
    <Description>GearGoblin is a BiS planner, gear inventory reader, and materia advisor for FFXIV that takes over the native Character window. As of v0.4.5 it ships as a full CharacterPanelRefined replacement: compact one-line derived stats per substat (Crit chance / damage multiplier / damage increase, Det damage increase, DH chance / damage increase, Tenacity damage and mitigation for tanks, Piety MP/tick for healers), breakpoint hints inline, real GCD under Skill/Spell Speed, and a Materia Advisor section under Gear that surfaces the top three meld actions. Plus the standalone /goblin window for Plan/Audit modes, Etro and XIVGear BiS comparison, /goblinexport for Tonberry Tactics handoff, and a /goblin-clickable header. Auto-detects CPR and steps aside if both are installed. Materia formulas re-derived from public datamining sources.</Description>
    <RepoUrl>https://github.com/LastOnionKnight/GearGoblin</RepoUrl>
    <Tags>gear;bis;materia;etro;xivgear;raid;advisor;cpr;character-panel</Tags>

    <Nullable>enable</Nullable>
    <LangVersion>latest</LangVersion>
    <AllowUnsafeBlocks>true</AllowUnsafeBlocks>
  </PropertyGroup>

</Project>
